<section id="the-bulbs" class="level1" data-number="2">
<h1 data-number="2"><span class="header-section-number">2</span> The Bulbs</h1>
<section id="the-bifurcation-of-the-quadratic-map" class="level2" data-number="2.1">
<h2 data-number="2.1" class="anchored" data-anchor-id="the-bifurcation-of-the-quadratic-map"><span class="header-section-number">2.1</span> The Bifurcation of the Quadratic Map</h2>
<p>The Bifurcation diagram of the Quadratic Map and the Mandelbrot set are linked and correspond to each other and the Quadratic Map is defined as: <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?x_%7Bn+1%7D=x_n%5E2+c"></p>
<p><strong>But what is a bifurcation diagram of the Quadratic Map?</strong></p>
<p>It shows how the long term behaviour of a system changes as a parameter is adjusted in the quadratic map.</p>
<p>Let’s take a value for <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c"> like <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c=0.2"> and look at its long term behaviour.</p>
<p><img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cbegin%7Baligned%7D%0Ax_0&amp;=0%20%5C%5C%0Ax_1&amp;=0%5E2+0.2%20&amp;&amp;=0.2%20%5C%5C%0Ax_2&amp;=0.2%5E2+0.2%20&amp;&amp;=0.24%20%5C%5C%0Ax_3&amp;=0.24%5E2+0.2%20&amp;&amp;=0.2576%20%5C%5C%0Ax_4&amp;=0.2576%5E2+0.2%20&amp;&amp;=0.2664%20%5C%5C%0Ax_5&amp;=0.2664%5E2+0.2%20&amp;&amp;=0.2710%20%5C%5C%0A%5Cend%7Baligned%7D%0A"></p>
<p>Here, we see the values converging to a single point at approximately 0.2764 which is called a fixed point. Taking a different value for <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c"> like <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c=0.5"> we see a different behaviour: <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cbegin%7Baligned%7D%0Ax_0&amp;=0%20%5C%5C%0Ax_1&amp;=0%5E2+0.5%20&amp;&amp;=0.5%20%5C%5C%0Ax_2&amp;=0.5%5E2+0.5%20&amp;&amp;=0.75%20%5C%5C%0Ax_3&amp;=0.75%5E2+0.5%20&amp;&amp;=1.0625%20%5C%5C%0Ax_4&amp;=1.0625%5E2+0.5%20&amp;&amp;=1.6289%20%5C%5C%0Ax_5&amp;=1.6289%5E2+0.5%20&amp;&amp;=3.1555%20%5C%5C%0A%5Cend%7Baligned%7D%0A"></p>
<p>Here, we see the values diverging to infinity, indicating that for <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c=0.5">, the system does not settle into a fixed point.</p>
<p>We can also do this for negative numbers like <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?c=-1">: <img src="https://latex.codecogs.com/png.latex?%0A%5Cbegin%7Baligned%7D%0Ax_0&amp;=0%20%5C%5C%0Ax_1&amp;=0%5E2-1%20&amp;&amp;=-1%20%5C%5C%0Ax_2&amp;=-1%5E2-1%20&amp;&amp;=0%20%5C%5C%0Ax_3&amp;=0%5E2-1%20&amp;&amp;=-1%20%5C%5C%0A%5Cend%7Baligned%7D%0A"></p>
<p>We can clearly see that the values cycle between -1 and 0, showcasing the behaviour of a period-2 cycle.</p>
</section>
