<section id="comparison-with-the-mandelbrot-set" class="level2" data-number="2.3">
<h2 data-number="2.3" class="anchored" data-anchor-id="comparison-with-the-mandelbrot-set"><span class="header-section-number">2.3</span> Comparison with the Mandelbrot set</h2>
<p>Now, if we overlay the bifurcation diagram on top of the Mandelbrot set as shown in Figure&nbsp;3, we can see that the bulbs of the Mandelbrot set correspond to the stable regions in the bifurcation diagram. The largest bulb at the center corresponds to the fixed point region, while the smaller bulbs going left correspond to period-2, period-4 cycles, and so on.</p>
